The inference part of the code doesn't work. The instructor doesn't respond to queries in the discussion forum either. After spending the whole time, I realised that it didn't work. Disappointed.
"â€‹AttributeError: module 'helper' has no attribute 'show_image' " (I tried installing the modules, but it is still not working).
As a course it didnot explain professionally.
it is too much step by step follow. it does not explain the why about what is happening within the project.being said that, it is good for just getting started.

Pretty good overall. Some work needed with this projects to make them easier to debug, such as making source code available with a diff tool so people can more easily pick out stupid types.Because this is python, not cpp or java or similar, it can actually be pretty hard to catch a lot of typos, due to lack of compile time checks, scope control, and abundance of global variables.
Great instructor and very practical hands-on approach. I would prefer more explanation on other encoder and weight presets as that will be important for transferring the knowledge learned here!
